#chapter(6, "The First Contact: How will Narumi Mona handle the task of interacting with strangers?")[
  "Hey Uta, did you see that?"

  "Yeah, I totally did not expect that to be real, but after this it is
  basically confirmed at this point..."

  "So... are we going to ask her or not?"

  // bruh
  "It would be very rude, though. Is there a manga about a girl with a terrible
  inferior complexity with her ultra-popular older sister?"

  "Hmm, you're right, she would think that we are only interested in her
  sister..."

  "But isn't it the case, though?"

  After a terrible self-introduction of a _certain_ blonde girl,
  quite a number of girls were discussing something, even though the
  self-introduction itself has nothing out of the ordinary.

  Nanba Mikoto were one of them.

  When the entrance exam results along with the class student list were publicly
  announced in the homepage of Misuzu High School, she found out a very peculiar
  thing about one of her future classmates.

  That surname.

  It was exactly the same one that her favorite model had.

  The same kanji characters, too.

  Initially, she turned it a silly joke and call that girl "the little sister of
  Narumi Sena", and not think much of it.

  "The little sister of Narumi Sena? Who? The girl from that selfie?"

  That nickname she given to one of her future classmates slipped out of her
  mouth when she was talking with Kazugai Uta, one of the few acquaintances that
  knew who "Narumi Sena" was.

  Ah, right, forgot to mention, but Narumi Sena was the model mentioned earlier.
  Ring some bells now?

  "It's just a inside joke of mine, haha..." Mikoto laughed, trying to cover up
  her lame joke, "Wait, what do you mean by _that selfie_?"

  "There was a selfie of hers taken with her little sister. It's quite old
  though. I was thinking you were mentioning that."

  "Wait, show me that!" Mikoto voice became enthuastic all a sudden, "And do you
  know what that little sister's name was?"

  "Heh-, what's with the sudden change? And no, there was only a little photo."

  And that began the tale of Detective Nanba Mikoto along with her assistance,
  Kazugai "Dr. Watson" Uta.

  They have no clues other than that picture, though. It was a complete roadblock.

  Until today.

  "The same hair color. The same family name. Not to mention that she looked
  exactly like that girl from the selfie. It has to be true."

  Mikoto's glance was fixated on the number-one suspect of being "the little
  sister of Narumi Sena", while her friend Uta, sitting on the desk above,
  were too busy with her smartphone.

  Annoyed but curious, Uta decided to drop the phone she was fidgeting with,

  "Well, should we go talk to her during lunch? I guess I can phrase it well for
  you so that she won't misunderstand."

  _"Not that there was anything to misunderstand in the first place."_

  Uta felt bad for the girl who was stared upon by her friend during the whole
  self-introduction session and the entrance ceremony, The girl did not seem to
  realize it, however.

  And that brought us up to the current moment. Lunchtime.

  _"Now that I had a closer look at her, she really does look like Narumi
  Sena. What's her name again? Right, Narumi Mona."_

  Narumi Mona really resembled her sisters' looks, but the problem was that she
  rarely wear the same smile her sister was having. So someone used to Narumi
  Sena's smiles would never think that this always-so-reserved Narumi Mona would
  be related to her.

  Now that Uta had a up-close look at this girl, she could say with 100%
  certainty that her friend's suspicions were right. Now, all what's left was to
  find out how her personality was like.

  Kazugai Uta had been used to initiating conversations with strangers. As a
  consequence, when her friends wanted to make contact with some people they did
  not know, she always became some sorts of third-party between the two.

  And because so, she had quite a lot of connections. All surface-level though.

  According to her, the first step, greeting, is the most crucial.

  "Hey, Narumi-san, wasn't it?" Uta said, confidently.

  The girl looked up in disbelief. Frozen, even.

  After a moment, which seemed like the time she needed to process the overload
  of information she just received, the girl replied with a soft tone.

  "Kazugai-san, wasn't it?" Her expression remained stiff, "Uhm, I'm Narumi."

  _"Wow, she actually remembered my name. If not for her background and
  Mikoto's silly detective game, I would never remember hers..."_

  Remembering names were a really hard thing to do, especially to most of the
  class that was paying no attention to the self-introduction game at all.

  Though, the reason that Mona remembered Uta's name was that, while Mona was
  trying to make a coherent self-introduction of her own, she had to took notes
  from that of others before her, and the name "Kazugai Uta" and its owner's
  overwhelming aura entered her mind, subconsciously.

  Just as Mona finished her incoherent answer, Uta grabbed both of her hands in
  great delight.

  "You remembered my name? Thank you very much!", Uta smiled brightly, a smile
  which could be comparable to that of an idol, "Ah, I wanted to ask you
  something, Narumi-san."

  Mona, whose hands were now tied in the tight grip of the girl standing before
  her, was definitely shocked by this development.

  After realizing Mona's slight discomfort from how tight the grip has come, Uta
  released her hands, trying to make Mona as comfortable as she could be.

  Even more nervous than before, she gulped before saying in a quieter voice
  than before, "Uhm, what is it?"

  Uta took a deep breath.

  It was time for the important question.

  “Are you, by any chance, the younger sister of Narumi Sena?”

  “Heh?”

  Uta's question caught the attention of the whole class, while the girl in
  front of her was in complete shock.

  There was nothing other than disbelief written on her face right now.

  _"Was I too insensitive? She might be weirded out..."_

  Meanwhile, on the other end...

  _"Sis? Why are they mentioning her here?"_

  Narumi Sena is a fashion model who had been quite struggling with her career
  since her high school days. Though she had a cute face and a beautiful figure,
  so did other models. Combined with the inflexible schedule of a high school
  student, the number of gigs she landed was not something too impressive.

  But she fought on with all her might. Keeping a detailed nutrition plan,
  waking up for a run every morning, often arrived home late, those were the
  extent of what she had done to keep her dream alive.

  And with all the efforts that she put in, she was blessed with a gift from God.

  After she graduated from high school, she landed a minor role in the popular
  // peaksama the (other) princess of #621 mentioned
  TV historical drama “The demise of a foolish princess”. Yes, she even had to
  do non-model jobs to stay relevant in the industry. Pretty standard stuff,
  though.

  She practiced like crazy for it. Not just acting, but she also analyzed every
  bit of the character she portrayed, in order to deliver the absolute perfect
  performance.

  And when the drama aired on TV, her acting had captured the hearts of millions,
  even though her role was supposed to be the supporting character.

  Thanks to that, she had practically become a celebrity, gained a massive and
  dedicated following, and no longer having to struggle for gigs. Now she had a
  new problem, which was to somehow managing her schedule in a way that could
  fit every job she was having.

  In other words, Narumi Sena was the Cinderella that became a princess just
  after a miraculous night.

  Though Mona knew all of this, she was not aware of the consequences of her
  sister’s popularity, and how it would affect her own life.

  Well, at least it made some people that should have _never_ been interested in
  her stop by and ask about her relationship with her sister.

  _"Hmm, with this newfound popularity, what should I do... Should I make my own
  crypto coin or something?"_

  That would severely damage your sister's reputation, though. And yours too.

  _"Anyway, I gotta reply to them, they surely are weirded out by this huge
  delay. Let's just come clean..."_

  During that time, Uta and Mikoto had traded eye contact a couple of times. Uta
  gave something like "Wait, did I do something wrong?", which was answered by a
  gaze that communicated "I don't know, what should we do?", followed by a "I
  don't know" gaze from Uta.

  "Narumi-san, are you okay?" Uta, whose question had been left unanswered for
  quite a while, worryingly asked Mona, who was still lost in her thoughts, "If
  it is uncomfortable for you..."

  "No, I’m fine, really. I was just shocked, after all.", Mona, finally recovered
  from her frozen state, mumbled, "Uhm, you were right, I’m her sister."

  "Really?"

  Mikoto unexpected jump into the conversation, leaving Mona speechless.

  Uta's overwhelming presence almost made Mona forget that there was yet another
  girl standing in front of her.

  Realizing how awkward things have become, Mikoto glanced back at Uta, asking
  for help, just to be given a "Hey, are you serious?" look.

  Without any other options, Mikoto turned her head back to the shocked Mona and
  introduced herself,

  "Erm-, I'm Nanba Mikoto, if you don't remember from the self-introduction
  thing..." she continued, her voice getting quieter and quieter, "Actually, I
  have a small request..."

  // what will her small request gonna be?
  // find out in the next novel writing session chat
]
